  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Remove or Hide Pagination Info Element\n\nRemove the `.pagination-info` element from the DOM or hide it using CSS to prevent it from displaying to users.\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate all instances of elements with the `.pagination-info` class in the codebase\n- Choose implementation approach: either delete the HTML/component code entirely or add CSS to hide it\n- If hiding with CSS, use `display: none` or `visibility: hidden` as appropriate\n- Verify the element is no longer visible on all pages where pagination appears\n- Ensure removal/hiding doesn't break any JavaScript that references this element\n- Check if any parent containers need layout adjustments after removal\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Multiple pagination instances on a single page\n- Different pagination implementations across different sections of the application\n- Any accessibility concerns if screen readers still announce hidden content",
